com.facebook.litho.animation

Class RenderThreadTransition

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.litho.animation.TransitionAnimationBinding
      • com.facebook.litho.animation.RenderThreadTransition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AnimationBinding

    public class RenderThreadTransition
extends TransitionAnimationBinding
    Animation for the transition of a single PropertyAnimation to be run on the render thread, while at the same time shadow the animation on the UI thread in order to keep AnimatedPropertyNode value in sync. If the delay is passed it will be considered as a part of the animation, and will be applied by creating an adjusted interpolator (you may consider using Transition.delay(int, Transition) ()} instead, but this way the delay will be handled on the UI thread)

      • collectTransitioningProperties

        public void collectTransitioningProperties(ArrayList<PropertyAnimation> outList)
        Description copied from interface: AnimationBinding
        Collects the set of PropertyAnimations that this animation will animate. This is used to make sure before/after values are recorded and accessible for the animation. Implementations should add their animating properties to this set. Note: This is a 'collect' call instead of a getter to allocating more sets then necessary for animations with nested animation (e.g. a sequence of animations). Yay Java.
